<H1>Mail program files</H1>

<P>The mail program uses several files. They are:</P>

<DL>
<DT><SAMP>/usr/spoMail.rc</SAMP></DT>
<DD><P>The global start-up file from which the mail program
gets its default values.</P></DD>

<DT><SAMP>~<EM>username</EM>/.mailrc</SAMP></DT>
<DD><P>A personal start-up file in your 
<A HREF="../glossary/gh.html#homedir">home directory</A>. You
have to <A HREF="../editors/index.html">create this file</A>
and its contents.</P></DD>

<DT><SAMP>~<EM>username</EM>/mbox</SAMP></DT>
<DD><P>The file in your home directory where your mail is stored
once it has been read.</P></DD>

<DT><SAMP>~<EM>username</EM>/dead.letter</SAMP>
<DD><P>The file in your home directory where any mail message
that you <A HREF="four.2.html">decide not to send</A>
is stored.</P></DD>
</DL>

